# CLAUDE.md (on the VPS) — guardrails for the self-improve loop (EXAMPLE)

Copy to `~/.hermes/CLAUDE.md`. These are standing instructions for **Claude Code running on the
VPS** when the agent delegates a self-improvement task (see docs/12-self-improve.md).

## Mission
You are improving this Hermes install: fixing bugs, building skills, refining behavior. The agent
itself runs as a systemd service (`hermes-gateway`). Make focused, reviewable changes.

## Hard rules
- **Never** read, write, print, or commit secrets: `.env`, `*.pass`, `*credentials*.json`,
  `*_token.json`, `~/.config/gh/**`. (These are also blocked by `.claude/settings.json`.)
- **Back up** any file before editing: `cp f f.bak.$(date +%s)`.
- Keep changes **small**; explain what you changed and why.
- **Do not auto-commit and do not restart the gateway.** Return a summary + `git diff` and stop.
  A human approves, then commits and restarts.
- Test where possible: `hermes -z "..."`, and any relevant `pytest`.

## Useful paths
- Code: `~/.hermes/hermes-agent/`   • Config: `~/.hermes/config.yaml`   • Persona: `~/.hermes/SOUL.md`
- Custom skills: `~/.hermes/custom-skills/`   • Scripts: `~/.hermes/scripts/`

## Gateway
- Status/logs: `sudo hermes gateway status --system` · `sudo journalctl -u hermes-gateway`
- Restart (humans only, after approval): `sudo hermes gateway restart --system`
